title: CBT Nuggets - Juniper JNCIS-SEC JN0-332
description:
Juniper Networks Certified Specialist Security (JNCIS-SEC) JN0-332 by Michael Shannon <a href="
https://secure.cbtnuggets.com/it-training-videos/series/juniper-networks-certified-security-specialist" rel="nofollow" target="_NEW">
https://secure.cbtnuggets.com/it-training-videos/series/juniper-networks-certified-security-specialist</a>


This video training with Michael Shannon covers the basics of Juniper Networks security technology, including Junos CLI for the SRX, Network Access Translation, and more.

Recommended skills:
Familiarity with Juniper Networks technology
Familiarity with SRX Series devices

Recommended equipment:
Junos software
SRX series devices

The Juniper Networks Certified Specialist Security (JNCIS-SEC) certification track allows you to show core competency with general Juniper Networks security technology and the Junos software for SRX Series devices.

In this CBT Nugget series from security expert Michael J. Shannon, you will explore: SRX appliance essentials, security zones, SCREEN options, security policy, NAT and PAT, IPSec VPNs, high availability clustering options, IDP, firewall user authentication, an introduction to UTM, anti-spam filtering, anti-virus protection, content and web filtering, and more. Plus, you'l be prepared to take the JN0-332 exam!
